            . I am a <rs id="t18310407-149-viclabel826" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-149-victim1190 t18310407-149-viclabel826"></join>. I lost some butter on the 20th of March; the Policeman brought this prisoner and another to me with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-149-person1192">
                  HENRY 
                  SANDERS
               <interp inst="t18310407-149-person1192" type="surname" value="SANDERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-149-person1192" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-149-person1192" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took this prisoner and Green (see page 397) in Upper Park-street, on the 20th of March - they were both running together; Green took off his hat, gave this butter to the prisoner, and I took them; they were then two hundred and fifty yards from the prosecutor's shop.</p>
               <p>RICHARD BROWN. I believe it was my butter, and it answered to the size of the piece that had been taken out of the tub, but I could not swear to it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I did not know it was stolen.</p>
